{
  "stem": "26111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because there was a glass cubicle at the end of the ward which had-- on top of a table, it had a children's bath.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everyone that left the ward had to be bathed in very antiseptic water, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I was, also.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the first time that my friends in the ward had perceived me naked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they saw, of course, that I was circumcised.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[WHISTLES] [LAUGHS] Absolutely amazing what these children knew about foreskins and about the details of this, that, and the other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, again, I have to add-- which I think is, I think, generally known, by this time-- that in Europe, people not-- unlike in America, men-- boys are not circumcised as a matter of course.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, in Germany at that time, certainly nobody was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe in the meantime, they've gotten more hygienically conscious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I doubt it very much because that is almost like a-- like a superstition.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so the only-- the, the-- it was your, your circumcisedness that betrayed you immediately as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There's a very interesting-- a very well-written story by-- and I wish I could remember the writer; it was published in America-- detailing the tribulations-- I think it's fictitious-- the tribulations of a boy in Poland, a Jewish boy in Poland, who, with his mother, hides out in different places, pretending-- the mother decides they don't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So she pretends to be non-Jewish-- Catholic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the fears that he goes through whenever he has to go into a public toilet, whenever he has to go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a bath is out of-- out of the question, public showers, anything like that, out of the question.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because that's the best way-- if they're in doubt, let your pants down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
